  "blurb": "A glass-walled, six-bedroom villa set among the rice fields ten minutes inland from Canggu's beaches, built around a 28-metre glass-bottomed pool with a swim-up bar — with a cinema, a karaoke room, a gym, a cold plunge and sauna, and open-plan living that dissolves into the green all around, hosting up to twelve with full staff and a private chef.",
  "detail": "Set among the rice fields a short drive inland from Canggu, this six-bedroom villa is a study in glass and greenery — floor-to-ceiling walls that fold the paddy views into every room, cascading water and warm wood tempering the modern lines. Six en-suite bedrooms sleep up to twelve, which makes it as comfortable for an extended-family holiday as it is for a celebration.\n\nThe grounds are built for long, unhurried days: a 28-metre glass-bottomed main pool with a swim-up bar, a second glass-bottomed pool off the master suite, and open-plan living and dining spaces that run straight out to the terrace. Indoors there is a cinema, a theatre room, a games room with a pool table, a karaoke room, a gym, and a cold plunge and sauna for winding down.\n\nA resident team keeps everything running — a private chef, concierge, security and gardeners — with airport transfers arranged on arrival. Canggu's beaches, cafés and beach clubs are about ten minutes away, close enough for a morning surf and far enough to keep the rice-field quiet.",
